{
  "texts": [
    "The brown graph reports the number of active users in each week.",
    "The blue (red) graph reports the number of users who switch to active (inactive), the green the number of users who switch to active for the first time, the purple the number of users who were active for the last time, i.e.",
    "drop out of the sample altogether.",
    "All graphs, but particularly the latter two, are skewed upwards respectively downwards towards beginning and end of the study period due to the nature of how the dataset is constructed.",
    "Hence, we drop the first and last three weeks for visualization purposes (137 total weeks left)."
  ]
}